cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with hyperspectral image classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves domain adaptation and active learning, which are both topics in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of multiple kernels and the Margin Sampling strategy also suggest a focus on algorithm development and optimization (cs.AI). The paper also involves feature extraction and analysis, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of hyperspectral images suggests a potential application in multimedia (cs.MM).
